# {{ project_name }}

Generated by **perfectRAG** — template `onyx-stack`.

[Onyx](https://github.com/onyx-dot-app/onyx) (formerly Danswer) is enterprise
**connector-based** search: it indexes your company's SaaS data — Slack, Google
Drive, GitHub, Confluence, Gmail and 40+ more — with permission-aware results.
Use this when the goal is *"chat over our company's tools"*, not *"chat over
uploaded PDFs"* (for the latter use `custom-naive-rag` or `ragflow-stack`).

## Stack

| Component | Choice |
|---|---|
| App API | `onyxdotapp/onyx-backend` — http://localhost:8080 |
| Web UI | `onyxdotapp/onyx-web-server` — http://localhost:3000 |
| Relational store | Postgres |
| Search index | Vespa |
| Cache/queue | Redis |

## ⚠️ This is a starting point

The compose here vendors Onyx's **data tier** + references the official app
images so you can get oriented. For a complete, production-grade deployment
(background workers, model servers, nginx, full env) use Onyx's upstream compose:

> https://github.com/onyx-dot-app/onyx/tree/main/deployment/docker_compose

## Quickstart

```bash
docker compose up -d
```

Open `http://localhost:3000`, then add connectors and configure your LLM in the
Onyx admin UI.
